1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper studies the ergodic capacity of a wireless network, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on a wireless relay network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the performance of a wireless network, which can be analyzed using systems and control theory. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper mentions the multicast scenario, which involves the transmission of multimedia content to multiple receivers. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper mentions the computation of the minimum vertex cut-set of the underlying graph, which can be done in polynomial time, indicating a connection to computational complexity.
